Sample_title: ATAC-seq in MSCs infected with EWSFLI1 (rep3)
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: 5x10^4 cells for each condition were first incubated in hypotonic buffer then resuspended in lysis buffer, centrifugated and resuspended in Transposase reaction mix for additional 30 min at 37C, following manufacturer recommendations (Nextera DNA sample Prep Kit, Illumina)., DNA was purified and adaptor sequences were added to the fragmented DNA by PCR to construct Illumina sequencing libraries. Purified PCR products were sequenced using the Illumina Nextseq device.
Sample_data_processing: Reads were aligned to hg19 using bwa. Reads that aligned in the proper orientation and on the same chromosome were then filtered to exclude PCR duplicates. Signal densities were calculated over a sliding 150 bp window at 20 bp steps and normalized to 10M reads in each experiment
sample_name: ATAC-seq in MSCs infected with EWSFLI1 (rep3)

Sample_title: HA ChIP-seq in A673 cell line infected with GFP
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Chromatin from formaldehyde-fixed cells (2-5 x 10^6 cells per epitope) was fragmented to a size range of 200 - 700 bases with a Branson 250 Sonifier. Solubilized chromatin was immunoprecipitated with the indicated antibodies and Protein G-Dynabeads (Life Technologies). Immunoprecipitated DNA was extracted with AMP Pure beads(Beckman Coulter) after crosslink reversal, RNAse A and Proteinase K treatment., ChIP DNA samples were used to generate Illumina sequencing libraries following standard protocols.
Sample_data_processing: Reads were aligned to hg19 using bwa (Li and Durbin, 2009). Aligned reads were then filtered to exclude PCR duplicates.
sample_name: HA ChIP-seq in A673 cell line infected with GFP
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Aligned reads were extended to 200 bp to approximate fragment sizes. Density maps were generated by counting the number of fragments overlapping each position using igvtools, and normalized to 10 million reads.
